{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1104: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $f(n)$ be the maximum possible chromatic number of a triangle-free graph on $n$ vertices. Estimate $f(n)$. Current best: The best bounds available are\\[(1-o(1))(n/\\log n)^{1/2}\\leq f(n) \\leq (2+o(1))(n/\\log n)^{1/2}.\\]The upper bound is due to Davies and Illingworth \\cite{DaIl22}, the lower bound follows from a construction of Hefty, Horn, King, and Pfender \\cite{HHKP25}. Prize: no. OEIS: A292528. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory.","id":"vf_39be5d9f18afa96a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1104.erdos_1104.variants.upper https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1104.erdos_1104.variants.upper.","id":"vf_a556e22e5dc8eab0","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1104.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_39be5d9f18afa96a","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1104","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_a556e22e5dc8eab0","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1104","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_a556e22e5dc8eab0","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_39be5d9f18afa96a","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0